A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Multi-Domain Intelligence (MDI) is the Army Intelligence Enterprise's overarching modernization framework that drives modernization priorities to field a ready Army
Intelligence team supporting Mission Command against all threats in Multi-Domain Operations (MDO). The MDI framework will allow intelligence professionals to
execute the intelligence cycle and associated doctrinal functions with increased speed, precision, and accuracy in both competition and conflict. The framework's
emphasis on modernizing sensors, enhancing data management practices, and advancing analytical trade craft through technology will support commanders' ability to
make sound, timely decisions, placing friendly forces in a position of decisive advantage.

 DD8: FY27 funding in the amount of $34.830M supports development of the Army Intelligence Data Platform (AIDP). AIDP enables situational development,
 understanding, and intelligence support to targeting from strategic and operational echelons to the tactical edge. It sets the Army's intelligence data foundation and
 enables intelligence analysis at echelon, using data from all domains. All Theater Armies use AIDP as the common intelligence picture (CIP) to directly feed their
 Combatant Commands' common operating pictures (COP). AIDP utilizes agile software development processes to deliver user-prioritized incremental capability
 releases.

 DD9: FY27 funding in the amount of $14.764M supports the modernization of Army Geospatial hardware and software capabilities. The funding will be used to continue
 the development of the Army Geo Data Fabric (AGDF) and the NextGen GEOINT Workstation (NGWS), both of which align to the Army Integrated Geospatial Enterprise
 Capability (AIGEC) requirements. The funding will also be used to initiate software development activities for One World Terrain - Operational (OWT-O). AIGEC and
 OWT-O deliver the Geospatial capabilities that provide Army systems with authoritative geospatial data. Further details available in classified quad chart.




