A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Army Intelligence Data Platform (AIDP) modernizes the Analysis and Exploitation capabilities of the Army Intelligence Enterprise. AIDP enables situational
development, understanding, and intelligence support to targeting from strategic and operational echelons to the tactical edge. It sets the Army's intelligence data
foundation and enables intelligence analysis at echelon, using data from all domains. All Theater Armies use AIDP as the common intelligence picture (CIP) to
directly feed their Combatant Commands' common operating pictures (COP). Processed AIDP intelligence is made available to tactical commanders to make real-time
battlefield decisions. AIDP utilizes agile software development processes to deliver user-prioritized incremental capability releases.

 The FY27 funds in the amount of $34.830 million will be used for the development, integration, and delivery of priority Army Intelligence capabilities in the Cloud and on
 edge devices. See Classified QUAD for more information.

 Details provided under separate cover.




